===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The territory of [[Eastern Europe]] inhabited by [[Rusyn]]s, on the slopes of the Carpathian Mountains in parts of Ukraine, Poland and Slovakia.
# {{lb|en|historical}} Lands inhabited by Ukrainians ([[Ruthenian]]s) of the former Austrian Empire kingdom of [[Galicia]] (1772–1918), corresponding to parts of Western Ukraine.
# {{lb|en|historical}} Western East-Slavic lands, including the principalities of Halych-Volynia and Kiev, which united with Lithuania and Poland (14th c–1772), corresponding to parts of Belarus and Ukraine.
# {{lb|en|historical}} [[Rus]], an East Slavic medieval state (880–12th c), corresponding to parts of Belarus, Russia, and Ukraine.

